Given that the initial temperature of the mixture for each trial is  \( 25.5^{\circ} \) C, calculate the enthalpy change of neutralisation of the reaction, in kJ mol \( ^{-1} \) .
(Density of the mixture = 1.00 g cm \( ^{-3} \) ;
specific heat capacity of the mixture = 4.18 J g \( ^{-1} \)  K \( ^{-1} \) ;
heat capacity of the expanded polystyrene cup : negligible)
